IPL Data Analysis Dashboard (2008–2024)
Project Overview

This project analyzes Indian Premier League (IPL) data to uncover insights about team performance, player statistics, and match trends.
The analysis is performed using Python with libraries like Pandas, Matplotlib, and Seaborn, and visualized through a various plots.

Key Objectives:
* Analyse the teams performance across seasons
* showcasing the top-scoring batters and bowlers of the League
* studying the trends in matches and patterns 
*evaluates the correlation between the toss-wins with winning of match

DATASET used:
matches.csv -> match level data (teams, winners, toss, season,etc;)
deliveries.csv-> ball-by-ball data (runs, wickets,batters,bowlers,players etc;)

(the dataset was retrieved from https://www.kaggle.com/datasets)

tech stack implemented:
core language: Python
libraries: Pandas, Numpy, Matplotlib,seaborn

